@AdvancedReasoner text
Use AdvancedReasoner for bounded meta-reasoning tasks where the runtime should reason explicitly about uncertainty, evidence quality, missing structure, normative review, or engine escalation instead of pretending the task is already a finite closed-world puzzle.
Prefer it for abductive, probabilistic, causal, argumentative, belief-revision, legal, scientific, optimization-routing, formal-proof-routing, SMT-fragment, pragmatic, analogical, ethical, and creative-evaluation tasks when a bounded local pass is still useful.
The body may be a direct natural-language problem, a structured rewrite brief produced by logic-eval, or a JSON envelope that pins result_mode, program, or generation settings.
Prefer direct AdvancedReasoner routing when the task already clearly belongs to one of these advanced reasoning families. Prefer HumanLikeReasoner instead when the task is already a finite rule, constraint, graph, search, or numeric problem that should be solved exactly by local symbolic composition.
The expected exit surface is a structured reasoner response returned through `ctx.returnResponse(...)`, not `ctx.emit(...)`.
